This framework completely circumvents that problem. The probability space in this framework is an extremely broad target—it does not require any precise sequence, but only that any molecular cluster (or coacervate, vesicle, polymer network) happens to possess the most primitive autocatalytic or self-maintaining compartmental function. In random collisions at the atomic level, a dozen types of atoms (C, H, O, N, S, P, etc.) can form almost infinitely many combinations—the more diverse the combinations, the more numerous the effective targets, not fewer.

